    <a href=search.php3?query=&topic=13&author=><img src=images/topics/scoop.gif border=0 Alt="Scoop/Info" align=left hspace=10 vspace=10></a>
    <p>Ad plagiarism doesn't get more blatant than Global PC's theft of one of the 
  most famous commercials in history-Apple Computer's "1984." DaBitch tipped me 
  to this heist recently and I investigated. (Apple's "1984" can be found in the 
  <a href=redirect.php3?op=redir&sid=23&url=http%3A%2F%2Fcommercial-archive.com>Commercial Archive</a> and Global PC's 
  ripoff is at <a href=redirect.php3?op=redir&sid=23&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.adcritic.com>Adcritic.com</a>.) </p>
<p>A shot by shot comparison of the two spots and an analysis of this criminally 
  insane act can be found at <a href=redirect.php3?op=redir&sid=23&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.commando.com>commando.com</a>. </p>
